Petar Raykov, Ethan Knights, & Rik Henson

5 Oct 2023

This script runs the analyses reported in the paper titled: Does functional system segregation mediate the effects of lifestyle on cognition in older adults?

Plot_regression_SyS <- function(MODEL,terms=~., Line_Col=rgb(0, 114, 178,maxColorValue =255),PointCol= rgb(112,191,235,maxColorValue = 255),PointSize=3,XLAB=NULL,YLAB=NULL,x_sc=0.1,y_sc=0.08,Beta=summary(MODEL)$coefficients[2,1],Tval=summary(MODEL)$coefficients[2,3],pval_temp=summary(MODEL)$coefficients[2,4],K=1,COND=list(),TITLE='',TYPE='conditional',HLINE=1,HSize=1,LINEWIDTH=2){

  if (pval_temp > 0.001) {
      p_value = sprintf('p = %.3f',pval_temp)
  } else {
    p_value = sprintf('p < 0.001')
  };
PLOT_VIS <- GGPLOTS <- vector('list', K)
PLOT_VIS[[1]] <- visreg(MODEL, terms,type=TYPE,partial=FALSE,rug=FALSE,gg=TRUE,
                   line=list(col=rgb(1,1,1,0)),cond=COND ) +
    geom_point(colour = PointCol,size=PointSize,alpha=0.7)+ 
  geom_smooth(method = 'lm', se = FALSE, color = Line_Col, formula = y ~ x, linetype = 'solid',linewidth=LINEWIDTH,alpha=0.7)+
 theme_classic() + xlab(XLAB) + ylab(YLAB)+
  theme(axis.text.x=element_text(face="bold",size=27),axis.text.y=element_text(face="bold",size=27), 
        axis.ticks=element_blank(),
        axis.title.x =element_text(size=35),
        axis.title.y =element_text(size=40)) 

yrange_c=layer_scales(PLOT_VIS[[1]])$y$range$range
xrange_c=layer_scales(PLOT_VIS[[1]])$x$range$range


PLOT_VIS[[1]]<-PLOT_VIS[[1]] + annotate('text',x=xrange_c[1]+(xrange_c[2] - xrange_c[1])*x_sc, 
                    y=yrange_c[2] - (yrange_c[2]-yrange_c[1])*y_sc, label=sprintf(' = %.2f\nT = %.2f\n %s',Beta,Tval,p_value),size=10) + 
  labs(title=TITLE) + theme(plot.title = element_text(size=40,face='bold',hjust=0.5))

if (HLINE == 1) {
  PLOT_VIS[[1]] <- PLOT_VIS[[1]] + geom_hline(yintercept=0,linetype='dashed',color='red',size=HSize)
}


PLOT_VIS}

Sex: 1 = males; 2 = females

Use SyS measure from three states (Movie, Rest, and SMT).

SyS was computed after GSR was performed and negative edges were zeroed. Similar to M. Chan et al., (2014)

Remove People with missing data on Behavioural measures and SyS

df_Schafer = df_Schafer[complete.cases(df_Schafer$CattellPCA), ]
df_Schafer = df_Schafer[complete.cases(df_Schafer$Memory_700), ]
df_Schafer = df_Schafer[complete.cases(df_Schafer$Rest_SyS), ]
df_Schafer = df_Schafer[complete.cases(df_Schafer$Mov_SyS), ]
df_Schafer = df_Schafer[complete.cases(df_Schafer$SMT_SyS), ]


df_Schafer$Sex = factor(df_Schafer$Sex)
levels(df_Schafer$Sex) <- c('Male','Female')

df_Schafer %>%

Make polynomial term for age

df_Schafer$ageQuad <- poly(df_Schafer$age,2) #1st linear, 2nd quad
df_Schafer$agepoly_1  = df_Schafer$ageQuad[,1]
df_Schafer$agepoly_2 = df_Schafer$ageQuad[,2]

df_Schafer$agepoly_1z  = datawizard::standardise(df_Schafer$agepoly_1) 
df_Schafer$agepoly_2z =  datawizard::standardise(df_Schafer$agepoly_2)

6) SyS should mediate the effect of mid-life activities on Cognition. (5.a) is not true but doing it for completeness Does SyS mediate effect of MA on Fluid Intelligence, older sample - Table 5

# REST
model_Fluid_MA_mediated_by_SYS_R <- '

# direct effect of MA
Cattell ~ c * MA +Age +SexC
# mediator SyS
Rest_SyS ~ a*MA 
Cattell ~ b*Rest_SyS 
## indirect effect (a*b)
ab := a*b
# total effect
total := c + (a*b)
'

fit_model_Fluid_MA_mediated_by_SyS_R <- sem(model_Fluid_MA_mediated_by_SYS_R, data = df_temp,bootstrap=5000)

parameterEstimates(fit_model_Fluid_MA_mediated_by_SyS_R, ci=TRUE,level=0.95,boot.ci.type="perc")

## SMT
model_EMemory_MA_mediated_by_SyS_S <- '
# direct effect of MA
Memory_700 ~ c * MA +Age + SexC
# mediator SyS
SMT_SyS ~ a*MA 
Memory_700 ~ b*SMT_SyS 
## indirect effect (a*b)
ab := a*b
# total effect
total := c + (a*b)
'

fit_model_EMemory_MA_mediated_by_SyS_S <- sem(model_EMemory_MA_mediated_by_SyS_S, data = df_temp,bootstrap=5000)

parameterEstimates(fit_model_EMemory_MA_mediated_by_SyS_S, ci=TRUE,level=0.95,boot.ci.type="perc")
